data.title: Michael Hartmann (soccer)
data.text:
American soccer player

Michael Hartmann (born June 13, 1994) is an American association football player who plays as a goalkeeper for Oskarshamns AIK in the Ettan Sodra.

Raised in Medford, New Jersey, Hartmann played prep soccer at Shawnee High School.[1]

Career

[edit]

College

[edit]

Hartmann played four years of college soccer at Division II school, Caldwell University between 2012 and 2015.[2] During his senior year, Hartmann was also part of the Ocean City Nor'easters side who competed in the USL PDL.[3]

Professional

[edit]

Hartmann had trials in Norway before joining 3. divisjon team Kolstad FK, but couldn't play with the team due to work permit issues.[4][5] He later has trials with Swedish fourth-tier side Link√∂ping City, who he signed with and played with for three seasons, achieving promotion to the third-tier in 2018.[6][7]

In January 2020, Hartmann joined Finnish top division side FC Haka.[8] He registered ten league appearances and eight in the cup before leaving the club.

In 2021, Hartmann returned to Sweden, signing with third-tier club, Oskarshamns AIK.
